Match/Components/Flag

Flag

A flag is a visual symbol that represents a country, state, union, or concept. Flags are in alphabetical order and have their ISO code at the end of their name. Svgs are adapted from this open source project: https://flagpack.xyz/

Figma
Github

Code

Usage

import { Flag, flagCodes } from "@twilio-labs/match/components";


const Component = () => <Flag code={"US"} />;

Props

PropTypeDefaultDescription
codestringnullThe specified flag code, see https://flagpack.xyz/docs/flag-index for reference
size?FlagSize'normal''small', 'normal', 'large'
decorative?booleanfalseDetermines if icon is decorative or informative. Decorative icon titles are not read by screenreaders.

Examples

Decorative Icons

alt text is provided for accessibility compliance unless the icon is specifically designated as decorative.

<Flag code={"US"} decorative={false} />

Sizes

<>
  <Flag code={"RAINBOW"} size={"small"} /> <Flag code={"RAINBOW"} />{" "}
  <Flag code={"RAINBOW"} size={"large"} />
</>

Flags

Flags of the countries and territories of the world.
Sizes: Small (12px), Normal (16px), Large (24px)

<div>
  {flagCodes.map(({ alpha2 }) => (
    <Flag code={alpha2} />
  ))}
